It seem that the most commonly asked question about savages right now is, &quot;Which race is best&quot;<br>
<br>
I noticed you play a troll, I personally play a kobold, and I see alot of klingon, er, Valkyn Savages on Pendragon.<br>
<br>
What are your thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trevanti>Trevanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage TL</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#000000>(11/27/02 9:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinedivinity.com/bilder/animations/assassin2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which race?</span><hr size=1> I think the reason you see a lot of Valkyn savages on Pendragon is because they're a novelty right now.  Everyone is checking out the new race.<br>
<br>
But Valkyn's don't really make good Savages.  Their Quickness is nice, but their Constitution is too low.  It's pretty balanced between the troll, the norse, and the kobold.  They all make good Savages with maxxed stats. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/trevanti/savagebanner5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xcbsmith>xcbsmith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(4/21/03 1:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What about Dwarves?</span><hr size=1> I'd think Dwarves would be awesome with their high con. What's wrong with them? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sammaeldarksbane>Sammael Darksbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(4/21/03 2:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about Dwarves?</span><hr size=1> HTH is based on Qui/Dex isn't it? and dwarves have a pretty lousy qui and dex... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raeloran@lighttanksofdaoc>Raeloran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#000000>(4/22/03 7:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about Dwarves?</span><hr size=1> Well, trolls are even worse in dex/qui. But look at the combined str and dex of each race since H2H is based on str/dex:<br>
<br>
Troll: 100 + 35 = 135<br>
Kobold: 50 + 70 = 120<br>
Norse: 70 + 50 = 120<br>
Valkyn: 55 + 65 = 120<br>
Dwarf: 60 + 50 = 110<br>
<br>
A dwarf savage would be the worst at H2H weapons. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raeloran Twinblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 50 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theravensclaw>The Ravens Claw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(5/10/03 1:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about Dwarves?</span><hr size=1> Well, since H2H is 50%Dex and 50%Str, those numbers might be a bit misleading to those who are just beginning play DAoC and decide to play a Savage.  Now, IMHO, on Str/Dex weapons, after adding the race's halved Dex and Str, you get the stat roughly equal to a character's Str stat if one was using a 100% Str weapon.  So here's the laydown on a races exact effectiveness using H2H weapons.  Remember the numbers are the Str and Dex halved.<br>
<br>
Troll<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ex16+Str50=66<br>
Dwarf<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ex25+Str30=55<br>
Norse<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ex25+Str35=60<br>
Kobold<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ex35+Str25=60<br>
Valkyn<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ex32+Str27=59<br>
<br>
Now we have the laydown for the classes base effectiveness using H2H.  Also take into account of the 30 Starting Points.  If someone wanted to go max offense, they would put 10 points into Str and Dex.  That would add 5 points into the halved Str and Dex, adding a total 10 points to the outcome.  Making the race's new H2H effectiveness as follows.<br>
<br>
Troll:76<br>
Dwarf:65<br>
Norse:70<br>
Kobold:70<br>
Valkyn:69(ehehehehe...pardon me, I'm a punk 13 year old.)<br>
<br>
Also one would need to put Qui in as a factor.  I picked up a attack speed calculation on some forum a few weeks ago.  The theory is, every 6 points of Qui above 60 is 1% haste.  So the calculation i as follows.<br>
(1-(qui-60)/400)weapon speed=attack speed.<br>
<br>
I have no idea of the truthfulness of the calculation, but I use it on my Mercenarys weaps and it seems to work rather well (And also makes me stop hating myself for putting 10 points into Str, Dex and Qui on start up.)<br>
<br>
So for level 35 or so and below, without items and buffs all races have a roughly equal damage output because of Qui.<br>
<br>
That said, the RA's and items a Savage might want to look into are of the following importance.<br>
1.Con(Studded Armor is sad...so very,very sad.)<br>
2.Qui(Sure, you get a point in it every two dings but a Savage is meant fly like a butterfly and sting like a bee)<br>
3.Str(Str adds to your weapon effectiveness but you only get a point every 3 dings)<br>
4.Dex(It may be important for parrying, evading and weap effectiveness, but you get a point every ding and you can afford to lay back a bit(barring if you're a troll, of course.)<br>
<br>
Also, Troll Savage's might wanna switch Con with Dex on that list.  70 Con is pretty nice, but 35 Dex will hurt your parry and evade.<br>
<br>
BTW peoples, I realize this is my first post, bt I've been playing this game since late 2001 and I like to think I know what I'm talking about.  Also, chances are I've just fabricated a big lie because of my arrogance as a stat master.  If any newbies rely on my post at all, I apoligize greatly if your toon ends up gimped.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Joe<br>
